    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on a high-ceiling matchup today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.88 score makes him our clear standout play. Facing Houser, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment and a significant platoon edge, making him the anchor of today\u2019s lineup. We also see strong value from **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.80) and **Marcell Ozuna** (67.58); the latter is particularly well-positioned in a favorable wind-out environment against Taillon, boosting his power projection significantly. While **Miguel Vargas** (64.07) is batting leadoff in a game with wind assistance, he remains a high-upside play that should pay dividends if he can leverage the park factors against Cameron.\n\nManaging our efficiency remains paramount, which led to a difficult decision regarding the bench. **Josh Jung** was the closest to cracking the starting nine with a 55.14 score, but he was ultimately squeezed out by the sheer efficiency of **Drake Baldwin** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who maintain better projected contact floors despite the threat of Woodruff. We must keep a close eye on the weather in our **Jackson Merrill** spot; the 39% rain risk at his venue adds volatility to his 58.20 score. Additionally, we are treading carefully with **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages** today; while both are high-caliber talents, facing the elite arm of deGrom suppresses their scores below the 60 threshold, though they remain must-starts given their roster status. We are monitoring the bench closely, keeping **Coby Mayo** and **Brady House** ready should lineup changes force a pivot away from the current projections.",
